\lim_{n\to\infty}\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{k}{n^2+k^2} .
\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{k}{n^2+k^2}=\frac{1}{n^2}\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{k}{1+\left(\frac{k}{n}\right)^2}=\frac{1}{n}\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{\frac{k}{n}}{1+\left(\frac{k}{n}\right)^2}\xrightarrow [n\to\infty]{}\int_0^1\frac{x}{1+x^2}\,dx=\ldots
\sum_{k=0}^nf(k,n)
f:[0,1]\to \mathbb{R}
f
U_{f,\mathcal{P}}=\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{k}{n^2+k^2}
\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{k}{n^2+k^2}=\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{f(x_k)}n
f(x_k)=\frac{kn}{n^2+k^2}\Rightarrow f(x)=\frac{xn^2}{n^2+n^2x^2}=\frac{x}{1+x^2}
